  "text": "The role of IgG4 in the pathogenesis of AIP is unknown. IgG4 accounts for the minority of total IgG in an individual. Uniquely, it can participate in half-antibody exchange reactions, where the heavy chain of one IgG4 molecule is replaced by another [CITATION_1] . This is facilitated by weak, non-covalent forces between the heavy chains of IgG4. The resulting bispecific-but functionally monovalentIgG4 is unable to bind antigens.",
